snippet.textDisplay:
Corbyn reminds me rather of Grand Maester Pycelle in Game of Thrones - he was an incompetent, irrelevant and morally dubious elderly member of the King's Council, who hung around like a bad smell for six seasons, outlasting three kings, and countless colleagues, most of whom were better and more intelligent men than he.

By season 6, we'd lost countless amazing characters, several of whom came to thoroughly undeserved ends...and amidst all the chaos, there was Pycelle, still shuffling around the palace doing the same old job (badly). He was mostly disliked, yet nobody cared enough to bother replacing him.

This is Corbyn. He's outlasted David Cameron and Theresa May. He's lost two general elections. Swathes of the Commons think he's an absolute joke, including lots of his own. And yet he's still there...droning on...
